A murder investigation is under way after a body was found outside a hospital. The body of a 56-year-old was left in a car which had been parked near the Good Hope Hospital in the Midlands. A 43-year-old man from Tamworth was arrested on suspicion of murder on  Friday night, according to West Midlands Police. Earlier in the evening, the body had been discovered outside the NHS hospital in Sutton Coldfield, near Birmingham. Police have identified the deceased 56-year-old but have not released his name. The car has been removed and is being scoured for forensic evidence. Police said a post-mortem examination will be carried out to confirm a cause of death. The victim’s family have been informed, a force spokesperson confirmed. Witnesses who may have information relating to the incident are being asked to come forward and speak to detectives. Alternatively, tip-offs can be made anonymously to Crimestoppers, with the possibility of a cash reward. Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.